Entropic
========

Entropic is a retro textmode blog theme for purists.

It is built as a modern Astro site, but the reading surface is intentionally
plain: fixed-width text, ASCII frames, ANSI-style color, volume indexes, and
`.phile` documents.


Quick Start
-----------

* Install dependencies:

        pnpm install --frozen-lockfile

* Run the local server:

        pnpm dev

* Check the site:

        pnpm check

* Build the static output:

        pnpm build

* Regenerate font assets after changing CJK coverage:

        pnpm assets:fonts


Essential Files
---------------

The usual entry points are:

* Site identity and home page text:

        src/config/site.ts

* Volume names, ordering, and postscripts:

        src/config/volumes.ts

* Textmode appearance:

        src/config/appearance.ts

* Motion effects:

        src/config/effects.ts

* Articles:

        src/content/philes/volume-*/**/*.phile

* Phile parser and rendering:

        src/modules/philes/
        src/modules/textmode/


Philes
------

Articles are written in `.phile` files. Each phile has YAML frontmatter and a
plain text body.

Required frontmatter:

* title
* date
* author

Optional frontmatter:

* order
* subtitle
* redacted

If `redacted: true` is set, the public route renders the redacted page. The
repository hook also unstages redacted philes before commit.


Volumes
-------

URLs are organized by volume:

        /volume/0/
        /volume/0/<phile-name>/

Volume configuration controls title, postscript, entry labels, and sorting.
If no explicit order is configured for a volume, philes sort by date descending.


Hooks
-----

Enable repository hooks in a fresh clone with:

        git config core.hooksPath scripts/hooks

The pre-commit hook scans staged `.phile` files and unstages any phile whose
frontmatter contains:

        redacted: true

The worktree file is not modified.


Deployment
----------

The site builds to static files and is deployed on Vercel.

The production build does not regenerate font assets. Generated font files and
CJK atlas assets are committed so Vercel does not need local font tooling such
as `pyftsubset`.
